## ğŸ—ï¸ AWS Infrastructure

### ğŸ”¹ AWS Global Infrastructure
> The complete worldwide network of AWS data centers that deliver secure, scalable, and low-latency cloud services.

### ğŸ”¹ AWS Regions
> Geographically separate locations around the world where AWS clusters its data centers to provide services close to users.

### ğŸ”¹ AWS Availability Zones (AZs)
> Multiple isolated data center groups within a Region, designed for high availability and fault tolerance.

### ğŸ”¹ AWS Data Centers
> Physical facilities housing servers, storage, and networking hardware that power AWS services.

### ğŸ”¹ AWS Edge Locations / Points of Presence
> AWS locations closer to end-users that accelerate content delivery through **CloudFront (CDN)** and reduce latency.

